---
description: Require a jargon glossary at the end of plan documents
alwaysApply: true
globs: "docs/**/*.md"
---

# Plan jargon glossary requirement

When producing or substantially updating a plan document (`docs/plans/`, `docs/inter-model/`, or any `*.plan.md` file), **append a `## Jargon TL;DR` section at the end** that defines every project-specific term, abbreviation, or coded phrase introduced or relied upon in the document.

## Format

```markdown
## Jargon TL;DR

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| F2a | Feature phase 2a — dedupe + ledger_id index for ask |
| Track A | Indexing the session chat transcript into convmem |
| Track B | Indexing a `logs/*.md` artifact into convmem |
```

## Rules

1. Include any term a new team member or a model seeing the project for the first time would not understand from context alone.
2. Cover lane names (Crush, Codex, Kiro, Cursor), phase codes (P0, P1a, F2a), shorthand (HITL, MCP, RSS in the watch-memory sense), taxonomy slugs (`feat/`, `wip/`, `docs/`), and any acronym or compound noun coined within the project.
3. Do NOT define universally-known terms (git, PR, CLI, API, JSON, etc.).
4. Keep definitions to one sentence max. Link to the canonical source if one exists.
5. If the document is a minor update (< 5 new terms, glossary already present), update the existing glossary rather than appending a duplicate.
6. The glossary goes at the very end of the document, after any `── Next steps ──` footer.
